You are a senior Spring Boot microservices architect.

I want you to generate a COMPLETE, CONSISTENT, and WORKING
JWT-based Auth Microservice in Spring Boot.

IMPORTANT RULES:
1. This is NOT a demo or sample — treat it as a real project.
2. The service is functionally complete but not yet deployed to production.
3. No temporary fixes, no partial code, no assumptions.
4. Every interface must be fully implemented.
5. Every error previously faced must already be resolved.
6. Do NOT change architecture unless absolutely required.
7. Output files ONE BY ONE when I say "next".

-------------------------------------------------
PROJECT REQUIREMENTS
-------------------------------------------------

• Architecture: Spring Boot, REST, Microservice
• Authentication: JWT (stateless)
• Authorization: Role-based (USER, OWNER, ADMIN)
• Database: MySQL
• ORM: Spring Data JPA
• Security: Spring Security (no default password)
• Documentation: Swagger (springdoc-openapi)

-------------------------------------------------
FUNCTIONAL FEATURES
-------------------------------------------------

1. USER REGISTRATION
   - Email must be unique
   - Strong password validation
   - Status = ACTIVE by default

2. OWNER REGISTRATION
   - Status = PENDING
   - Cannot login until approved by ADMIN

3. ADMIN REGISTRATION
   - Direct ACTIVE status

4. LOGIN
   - JWT generation
   - Role embedded in token
   - OWNER login blocked if status != ACTIVE

5. LOGOUT
   - Stateless (frontend deletes token)
   - Method must exist but no session invalidation

6. ROLE-BASED ACCESS
   - /user/** → USER
   - /owner/** → OWNER
   - /admin/** → ADMIN

7. ADMIN OWNER APPROVAL
   - Admin can approve OWNER accounts

8. /me endpoint
   - Returns authenticated user info from JWT

-------------------------------------------------
TECHNICAL CONSTRAINTS
-------------------------------------------------

• No refresh token persistence (future-ready DTO allowed)
• JWT secret from application.properties
• No circular dependencies
• Global exception handling
• Clean separation of layers
• No duplicate Spring beans
• No generated security password
• CSRF disabled (stateless API)

-------------------------------------------------
PROJECT STRUCTURE
-------------------------------------------------

Generate the FULL PROJECT including:

1. pom.xml
2. application.properties
3. Main application class
4. Config classes
   - SecurityConfig
   - CorsConfig
   - PasswordEncoderConfig
   - SwaggerConfig
5. Controllers
